The input for the system should be an array of strings.The input array, when passed to the system, should be regarded as an English Dictionary.The longest word in the input array should be found by the system.The determination should be made by the system if it is possible to construct the longest word by adding one character at a time using other words in the array.In the case where there is more than one possible answer, the system should return the longest word with the smallest lexicographical order.If the result is null, the system should return an empty string.